F. MARKET ACCESS


Import Climate

Poland signed an Association Agreement with the European Community (now
European Union - EU) in November 1991.  Trade provisions are expected to
eventually create a free trade area with the EU and a reduction of tariffs
rates for EU products and services.  New cars and commercial vehicles (HS
8703, and also HS 8704) imported from the USA currently have higher custom
duty rates as those imported from EU countries.

Customs Duty

The general customs rate for automotive imports from GATT countries is 35% of
CIF price.  Cars imported from EU, EFTA & CEFTA countries enjoy currently a
preferential rate of 30% of the CIF price.  Automotive imports to Poland sold
under Duty-free Quota are subject to 0% customs rate.  The minimum amount of
customs duty on new and up to four years old cars is ECU 1,250  (1 ECU =
$1.12). Automobiles older than 4 years are subject to the same customs rate,
but the minimum amount is ECU 2,500.


Under the Association Agreement with the European Union, it was agreed that
customs duty rates on automobiles imported from the EU countries to Poland
will be steadily reduced until they reach zero in the year 2002.

Border Tax

All vehicles are subject to a 6% border tax calculated on CIF price basis
increased by customs duty.

Excise Tax

A 15% excise tax is applicable if the CIF price is equal or exceeds ECU
7,000.  This tax is based on CIF price increased by 35% customs duty (even if
the customs duty is not applicable - 0% or if preferential 30% duty is
applicable) and 6% border tax.

VAT

A 22% VAT is calculated on CIF price increased by customs duty, border tax,
and excise tax (if applicable).

Duty-free Quota

Under the Association Agreement with the European Union, it was also agreed
that duty-free quotas for cars manufactured in EU countries and imported to
Poland will be established.  Each year the duty-free quota is supposed to
increase .  Starting in 1992 through 2001 the quotas granted by Poland will
allow a total 317,000 new, duty-free vehicles into Poland.  Duty-free cars
are allowed into Poland in lots of up to 400 units.  This means that each
official importer can apply for each lot separately, after the previous lot
is sold.

