Import Restrictions

There are certain import restrictions that apply to vehicles.  It is
forbidden by law to import cars older than 10 years and trucks older than 3
years.  It is also forbidden to import cars with two-stroke-engine into
Poland.

Vehicles imported to Poland have to meet certain requirements known as the
national type-approval system (homologation).  This system was established as
a partial adaptation of the EU directives.  In force since 1983, the national
type-approval system covers vehicles as well as parts.  The Polish
"Road Traffic Law" (February 1, 1983, published in "Dziennik Ustaw" on
February 6, 1992) obliges manufacturers and importers of vehicles, their
equipment and parts, to receive the type-approval granted by Minister of
Transport and Maritime Economy.  The certification agency appointed by the
Ministry tests the product and determines whether the product is consistent
with Polish standards and therefore can be sold in Poland.  The national
type-approval system in Poland is closely connected to the international EU
system (Poland partly adopted the EU directive 70/156/EEC on national
type-approval system).  Currently, there are 48 EU Regulations and 48
national standards which exist in Poland (distribution: active safety - 22 EU
Regulations, 8 national Standards; passive safety - 9 EU Regulations, 11
national Standards; environmental protection - 11 EU Regulations, 4 national
Standards; other safety features - 6 EU Regulations, 25 national Standards).


